{
  "texts": [
    "Given a corpus set Tthat includes a limited number of sentences S 1;...; S n f g, the purpose of low-resource Chinese NER is to generate entity labels for character c i in the sentence S based on T, thereby identifying entities c i;...; c j È É with specific meanings.",
    "Entity recognition processThe NER model often comprises of the embedding, encoding, and decoding layers, as shown in Figure 1.Embedding layer.",
    "The input to the embedding layer is a sentence S ¼ c 1; c 2;...; c N f g, where c i 2 R v is the one-hot vector representation of ith character, the v is vocabulary size.",
    "The output of this layer is a real-valued dense vector, e i, where each dimension represents a latent feature.",
    "Thus, the embedding representation of the sentence S is E ¼ e 1; e 2;...; e N f g. The embedding representation e i captures the semantic and syntactic properties of sentences automatically, which are not explicitly present in the one-hot vector representation c i."
  ]
}